<exercise checkit-seed="0035" checkit-slug="M4" checkit-title="Finding a matrix inverse">
  <statement>
    <p>Show how to find the inverse of the matrix <m>M= \left[\begin{array}{cccc}
2 &amp; -5 &amp; 5 &amp; 0 \\
0 &amp; 1 &amp; -2 &amp; -3 \\
-1 &amp; 2 &amp; -1 &amp; 3 \\
-2 &amp; 5 &amp; -8 &amp; -8
\end{array}\right] </m>.</p>
  </statement>
  <answer>
    <me>M^{-1}= \left[\begin{array}{cccc}
3 &amp; 5 &amp; 5 &amp; 0 \\
-10 &amp; -6 &amp; -14 &amp; -3 \\
-11 &amp; -8 &amp; -16 &amp; -3 \\
4 &amp; 3 &amp; 6 &amp; 1
\end{array}\right] </me>
  </answer>
</exercise>

